ed, there is no substitute for truth, in this or any case.\n\n- Ellis Peters, The Raven in the Foregate\n|\nThe secret does not lie in the perfection of your path, but in recognizing its imperfection.\n\n- Krist Pauwels, Your Work and Your Life: Towards a True Win-Win\n|\nIn the pursuit of knowledge, we know God, the source of knowledge and wisdom.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nAlthough a decision is often viewed as the turning point, it is action that creates tangible results.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nThe past is a place of reference, not a place of residence; the past is a place of learning, not a place of living.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nSome stories always remain incomplete, until you do not read them complete with heart <3\n\n- Danish\n|\nLove doesn't just sit there, like a stone, it has to be made, like bread; remade all the time, made new.\n\n- Ursula K. Le Guin, The Lathe of Heaven\n|\nWithin every elaborate lie, a kernel of truth.\n\n- Marisha Pessl, Night Film\n|\nWhere there is competition, one cannot attain (true) 'Knowledge'.\n\n- Dada\n|\nSince your life evaporates quickly, it is wisdom to learn how to number your days. Not just to number your days but to make each passing day productive.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nNever say that I have taken it, only that I have given it back.\n\n- Epicurus\n|\nHead up, heart open. To better days!\n\n- T.F. Hodge, From Within I Rise: Spiritual Triumph Over Death and Conscious Encounters with 'The Divine Presence'\n|\nIn the case of good books, the point is not to see how many of them you can get through, but rather how many can get through to you.\n\n- Mortimer\n|\nAs soon as you have made a thought, laugh at it.\n\n- Lao\n|\nThe longer we live, the more weight we carry in our hearts.\n\n- Ai\n|\nLife is pain, highness. Anyone who says differently is selling something.\n\n- William Goldman, William Goldman: Four Screenplays with Essays\n|\nWhen something is dirty you wash it. That's what my mum always said.Yet...When you have dirty money and you launder it, people jump up and down.I guess that's life.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nWhat we could consider magic, may just be science that we don’t understand yet.\n\n- Patricia Robin Woodruff, Strange Tales of Floyd County, VA\n|\nGod created you to be love, not abused.\n\n- Napz\n|\nWhoever doubt, hardens his own heart.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nIt is not necessary to be large to be a perfectly good arthropod (or mollusc, come to that).\n\n- Richard Fortey, Trilobite: Eyewitness to Evolution\n|\nWhole life is a search for beauty. But, when the beauty is found inside, the search ends and a beautiful journey begins.\n\n- Harshit\n|\nJust a minute, Cosmic Ordering can give you a whole lot more ... a whole lifetime of more.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering Guide\n|\nWith faith, you may get stuck in a very big lie and may lose the truth forever; but with doubt, you can always reach the truth!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nWhatever is worthy of adventure, can only be experienced.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWhen a group of people get up from a table, the table doesn’tknow which way any of them will go.\n\n- Galway Kinnell, Three Books: Body Rags; Mortal Acts, Mortal Words; The Past\n|\nFear not! In life, problems are there to make you stronger.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nGod abandons only those who abandon themselves, and whoever has the courage to shut up his sorrow within his own heart is stronger to fight against it than he who complains.\n\n- George Sand, La Petite Fadette\n|\nEducation: that which reveals to the wise, and conceals from the stupid, the vast limits of their knowledge.\n\n- Mark\n|\nI always say, 'Books beat boredom,' said Amanda wisely.\n\n- Mo Willems, Hooray for Amanda & Her Alligator!\n|\nRisks may make you win, or they will make you learn. Either of the benefits is worth daring for.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Become a Better You\n|\nWe can't believe what we believe to be untrue, and we can't love what we believe to be unreal.\n\n- Peter Kreeft, Pocket Handbook of Christian Apologetics\n|\nSee beyond the eyes can see, believe beyond the inspiration!\n\n- Felix Y. Siauw, Beyond The Inspiration\n|\nI can talk to fish!' Angel said happily, water dripping off her long, skinny body. 'Ask one over for dinner,' Fang said, joining us.\n\n- James Patterson, School's Out—Forever\n|\nA teacher will be frustrated if she is only motivated to teach what she has learned. Yet, if she is motivated because of the students, then she will learn from them how to teach.\n\n- Tanya R. Liverman, Memoirs of an Educarer: An Inspiration for Education\n|\nOur world is built on biology and once we begin to understand it, it then becomes a technology\n\n- Ryan\n|\nStanding on the defensive indicates insufficient strength; attacking, a superabundance of strength.\n\n- Sun Tzu, The Art of War\n|\nIf you aren't the woman I think you are, then this isn't the world I thought it was.\n\n- Arthur Golden, Memoirs of a Geisha\n|\nTwo minds with but a single thought, two hearts that beat as one.\n\n- Jasper Fforde, First Among Sequels\n|\nWe must serve the Lord, our God with all our heart, with all our soul and in everything be devoted to Him\n\n- Sunday\n|\nThere is a science to living well and art to experiencing the good life, and it begins with wisdom.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nI ask myself: is every story that has ever been written in this world, a story of suffering and affliction?\n\n- Clarice Lispector, The Hour of the Star\n|\nSome people grow older and more cynical. Some people become just the opposite. Life hurts without hope, and cynicism, once a luxury, becomes unaffordable.\n\n- William Norwich, My Mrs. Brown\n|\nAs long as there was coffee in the world, how bad could things be?\n\n- Cassandra Clare, City of Ashes\n|\nCheer up everyone,' he said, a new brightness to his voice. 'Since we’re all going to die horribly anyway, what’s there to be worried about?\n\n- Derek Landy, Skulduggery Pleasant\n|\nThere were a hundred shades between a truth and lie, and she knew them all.\n\n- V.E. Schwab, A Conjuring of Light"